definitions: the production of more of a product, commodity, or substance than is wanted or needed

examples.text: there was a crisis of overproduction in traditional manufacturing
certain foods cause overproduction of bacteria in the stomach

shortDefinitions: production of more of product etc. than is wanted or needed

definitions: the recording or arrangement of a song or piece of music in such an elaborate way that the spontaneity or artistry of the original material is lost

examples.text: so many tracks suffer from overproduction

shortDefinitions: recording of song in overly elaborate way
